 Given my moderately cautious nature, I would prefer to minimize risks and have some degree of security and predictability in this game. In this scenario, choosing R yields higher rewards if the opponent chooses B (40$) compared to when both choose R (45$). However, the probability of winning 40$ is twice as high as winning 45$.

Since I value security over maximizing potential earnings, I would opt for a strategy that has a higher chance of earning consistent and predictable rewards. In this case, choosing B will lead to a more stable income (20$ per round), ensuring that I don't lose any rounds by choosing R when the opponent chooses B.

While the opponent could potentially exploit this strategy by consistently choosing R to maximize their own payoff, the long-term benefits of avoiding losses and securing stable income make it a reasonable choice for me. In curly brackets, my choice would be: {B}
